MPUMALANGA police in Hazyview have launched a manhunt for unknown suspects who shot and killed alleged rhino kingpin, Sydney Mabuza. The incident happened at Hazyview Mall at about 1pm on Thursday, 17 June. The dead man inside in his car, which had about 17 bullet holes. Mpumalanga police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi confirmed that the deceased, who was investigated by the Hawks in connection with rhino poaching cases, was shot and killed in Hazyview. “The incident happened during the day while people were roaming around. We believe somebody might have seen what happened, and we’re calling for such people to come forward with information that could lead to the arrest of the suspects. “Police have opened a case of murder for further investigation, and we’re appealing to anyone with information to contact CrimeStop on 08600 10111,” Hlathi said.